Move these unrelated changes to a different commit
whitespace error here and in other files

This might be more readable if you capture the bytes in a bash array, slice the ones you need, then print them out.

```
rsp=($(i2cget -y -f -a 13 0x76 0x00 i 5))
ver=$(printf '%02X.%02X.%02X.%02x' ${rsp[6]} ${rsp[5]} ${rsp[4]} ${rsp[3]})
```
you should make a separate variable for the bus and address so you can use it throughout

I suggest copying the findmtd function from here instead: https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/18395e413e737ee78798497582bdd1ca104019e0/meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/initrdscripts/files/obmc-init.sh#L26
do we have `readlink` in our busybox? that'd be less flaky than using `ls`
Move these unrelated changes to a different commit
Also you may want to make a fw packagegroup
This file is already added in parent commit https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/40781/9

Since these components are moved here, these can be removed from the
meta-fii/meta-kudo/recipes-phosphor/image/obmc-phosphor-image.bbappend file.

Don't need this "WantedBy=" as the configuration json directly uses the "phosphor-ipmi-flash-bios-update.service " https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/40819/19/meta-fii/meta-kudo/recipes-kudo/kudo-fw-utility/kudo-bios-update/config-bios.json#16
Store them as decimals instead of hex
retain the bash array as patch 17.
